# Frontend (TypeScript / Next.js)

Stack: Next.js App Router, TypeScript, Tailwind, shadcn/ui, React Hook Form, TanStack Query, Zod.

## Rules

- No business logic inside components.
- No `fetch()` inside components — use an API service abstraction.
- Reusable components, prefer composition.
- Strict TypeScript. Never use `any`. Prefer interfaces. Use `readonly` where appropriate. Avoid unnecessary state.

## UI Design

- Follow `docs/design_system.md` (visual language) and `docs/design_tokens.md` (semantic tokens) for all UI. Do not invent colors, spacing, typography, or component styles.
- Brand: **TR!BE**. Theme: Dark-first.
- Use semantic token classes (`bg-primary`, `text-muted`, `border-border`) — never raw hex like `#F04E37` in components.
- Design language: premium, minimal, modern, high contrast, event-industry.
- Component library: shadcn/ui only; customize via the Tailwind theme.
- Avoid generic Bootstrap admin dashboards.
